  "local_port": 39606,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why is my fridge not working but my freezer is?",
  "response": "If your fridge is not working but your freezer is, it may be due to several potential issues. Here are some common causes:\n\n1. **Evaporator Fan:** The evaporator fan circulates cold air from the freezer to the refrigerator compartment. If this fan is not working, the fridge compartment may not receive the cold air it needs to stay cool.\n\n2. **Air Damper:** The air damper controls the flow of cold air between the freezer and the fridge. If the damper is stuck closed or malfunctioning, it could prevent cold air from getting to the fridge compartment.\n\n3. **Thermistor or Temperature Sensor:** This component monitors the temperature in the fridge and signals the control board to regulate the cooling process. If the thermistor is faulty, it may not be sending the correct signals to maintain the proper temperature in the fridge.\n\n4. **Defrost System:** A malfunctioning defrost system could cause ice buildup in the evaporator coils, which would affect airflow. If the defrost heater, defrost timer, or defrost thermostat is not functioning properly, it could lead to ice accumulation that blocks air transfer to the fridge.\n\n5. **Condenser Coils:** Dirty or dusty condenser coils can reduce the efficiency of the cooling system. These coils should be cleaned regularly to ensure they are operating efficiently.\n\n6. **Condenser Fan:** If the condenser fan is not working, it can cause insufficient cooling. This fan helps remove heat from the coils, and if it\u2019s not functioning properly, the fridge may not get cold enough.\n\n7. **Control Board:** The refrigerator's control board regulates the compressor, fans, and other components. A malfunctioning control board could lead to cooling issues in the fridge compartment.\n\nTo troubleshoot further, you may want to:\n- Check if the evaporator fan is running when the freezer is working.\n- Ensure there is no ice buildup blocking the vents between the fridge and freezer.\n- Verify that the temperature settings are correct.\n- Clean the condenser coils.\n- Listen for any unusual noises that could indicate a faulty fan or other components.\n- Consider seeking professional repair assistance if you are unable to diagnose or fix the problem yourself.\n\nIf you're uncomfortable performing these checks or if the problem persists, it may be best to consult a professional appliance repair technician.",
